00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:24,474
By the morning, V1 will be toast.

518
00:20:24,557 --> 00:20:25,892
Where are you going?

519
00:20:25,975 --> 00:20:28,353
Got to cut my tracking chip out.

520
00:20:28,436 --> 00:20:29,896
Never coming here again.

521
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,314
It's time for phase three.

522
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:32,982
- Wait, but what should I...
- [door opens]

523
00:20:33,066 --> 00:20:35,526
A-Are you really just leaving me here?

524
00:20:39,447 --> 00:20:40,949
Fuck.

525
00:20:41,032 --> 00:20:43,952
[old-timey music playing]

526
00:20:44,035 --> 00:20:45,954
What's got you looking blue, little lady?

527
00:20:46,037 --> 00:20:50,959
Gee, Bombsight, it's just, Henry's
noticed that I've put on a few pounds.

528
00:20:51,042 --> 00:20:52,502
Gettin' hefty, are you?

529
00:20:52,585 --> 00:20:56,839
You must not be using
Vought Brand Weight Control Tablets.

530
00:20:56,923 --> 00:21:00,677
Just take one with breakfast,
or better yet, instead of breakfast!

531
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:05,306
Our patented methamphetamine formula
will melt away that ugly belly fat

532
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:07,016
and give you pep in your step.

533
00:21:08,101 --> 00:21:10,228
[Mary-Beth] Thanks, Bombsight!
Henry will be thrilled!

534
00:21:10,311 --> 00:21:12,063
[Bombsight] You bet he will.

535
00:21:16,234 --> 00:21:17,193
Shit.

536
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:20,238
Hey, Goldie.

537
00:21:20,321 --> 00:21:21,364
Night night.

538
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:25,284
[Golden Geisha sighs]

539
00:21:25,368 --> 00:21:28,329
[grunting, panting]

540
00:21:33,126 --> 00:21:36,004
[old-timey music continues]

541
00:21:36,087 --> 00:21:38,089
[mysterious music playing]

542
00:21:39,841 --> 00:21:41,843
♪ ♪

543
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:02,030
Not so fast, white man.

544
00:22:11,748 --> 00:22:13,041
This one's for you, M.

545
00:22:13,124 --> 00:22:14,500
Fuck you.

546
00:22:19,422 --> 00:22:21,424
- [♪ Chic sings "Le Freak"]
- ♪ Ah, freak out ♪

547
00:22:21,507 --> 00:22:23,259
♪ Le freak ♪

548
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:24,427
♪ c'est chic ♪

549
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:25,678
♪ Freak out ♪

550
00:22:25,762 --> 00:22:27,263
[grunting]

551
00:22:29,307 --> 00:22:32,977
♪ Have you heard about
the new dance craze? ♪

552
00:22:33,061 --> 00:22:33,978
Stop.

553
00:22:34,062 --> 00:22:36,898
♪ I'm sure you'll be amazed ♪

554
00:22:36,981 --> 00:22:38,483
♪ It's called Le Freak...

555
00:22:38,566 --> 00:22:40,151
[screaming]

556
00:22:41,527 --> 00:22:43,071
[choking]

557
00:22:44,072 --> 00:22:45,531
♪ Ah, freak out ♪

558
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,366
No! You'll kill him!

559
00:22:47,450 --> 00:22:49,285
♪ C'est chic, freak out ♪

560
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:51,079
[Kimiko cries out]

561
00:22:53,081 --> 00:22:57,001
♪ Just come on down to the 54 ♪

562
00:22:57,085 --> 00:22:59,712
♪ And find a spot out on the floor ♪

563
00:22:59,796 --> 00:23:01,839
♪ Ah, freak out ♪

564
00:23:01,923 --> 00:23:04,759
What is taking you so long-- Oh.

565
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:10,348
[groans]

566
00:23:19,899 --> 00:23:22,068
[Soldier Boy] You sure
this is the right address?

567
00:23:22,151 --> 00:23:23,194
[Homelander] I'm sure.

568
00:23:24,612 --> 00:23:28,157
Well, there's no sign of Bombsight...
or fucking anyone.

569
00:23:28,241 --> 00:23:31,202
Maybe Crime Analytics got a bad tip.

570
00:23:39,293 --> 00:23:41,045
[moaning over video]

571
00:23:41,129 --> 00:23:43,464
[Homelander] Come on, rub it.
Rub it with your stump.

572
00:23:43,548 --> 00:23:45,216
Oh, yeah, just like that.

573
00:23:45,299 --> 00:23:48,052
- [Stormfront speaking German]
- [Homelander] Oh...

574
00:23:48,136 --> 00:23:51,305
- [Stormfront continues in German]
- [squishing]

575
00:23:51,389 --> 00:23:52,598
[laptop closes]

576
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:55,643
What the fuck was that?

577
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:57,103
I can explain.

578
00:23:57,186 --> 00:23:59,939
That was Clara.
You told me she killed herself.

579
00:24:00,022 --> 00:24:02,733
She did.
After Ryan did that to her.

580
00:24:02,817 --> 00:24:04,068
- It's his fault.
- So then, what,

581
00:24:04,152 --> 00:24:05,528
you locked her in your apartment

582
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:07,572
- like some kind of amputee fuck doll?
- No.

583
00:24:07,655 --> 00:24:09,866
- And filmed her for kicks?
- No. No. No!

584
00:24:09,949 --> 00:24:12,160
It wasn't like that. I did...

585
00:24:12,243 --> 00:24:14,787
I did everything I could
to-to keep her alive,

586
00:24:14,871 --> 00:24:17,456
to-to make her happy-- [grunts]

587
00:24:18,708 --> 00:24:20,501
[Homelander groans softly]

588
00:24:20,585 --> 00:24:22,211
[sniffles] Just listen to me.

589
00:24:22,295 --> 00:24:25,590
Okay, it wasn't all like... that.

590
00:24:29,802 --> 00:24:31,179
I couldn't let her go.

591
00:24:32,638 --> 00:24:33,931
I didn't know how.

592
00:24:36,642 --> 00:24:38,186
Because I loved her.

593
00:24:40,479 --> 00:24:41,772
And so did you.

594
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:46,485
You're goddamn right I loved her.

595
00:24:46,569 --> 00:24:48,863
She wouldn't want us fighting over her--

596
00:24:48,946 --> 00:24:50,323
Don't fucking tell me what she would want.

597
00:24:50,406 --> 00:24:54,327
You knew her for five minutes,
I was with her for decades.

598
00:24:54,410 --> 00:24:56,245
Hold-hold-hold on.

599
00:24:56,329 --> 00:24:58,080
This-this is a setup.

600
00:24:58,164 --> 00:25:00,750
Someone's trying to separate us.

601
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,585
This has been plan--

602
00:25:02,668 --> 00:25:05,213
Fucking Sage.

603
00:25:05,296 --> 00:25:06,297
It's Sage.

604
00:25:07,256 --> 00:25:08,799
You see?

605
00:25:08,883 --> 00:25:10,384
She's trying to screw with us.

606
00:25:10,468 --> 00:25:13,763
Oh, come on.
I can't find the V1 without you.

607
00:25:22,772 --> 00:25:23,773
Good.

608
00:25:26,901 --> 00:25:28,653
You don't deserve to live forever.

609
00:25:34,242 --> 00:25:37,870
[suspenseful music playing]

610
00:25:43,834 --> 00:25:46,212
- [beeps]
- [sighs] Security cameras are looped.

611
00:25:56,222 --> 00:25:57,390
[Annie] Who are they?

612
00:25:58,474 --> 00:26:00,059
It's almost every psychic in the country.

613
00:26:00,142 --> 00:26:03,062
What the fuck does Homelander
want with all of them?

614
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:06,065
[distant voices]

615
00:26:18,536 --> 00:26:20,538
♪ ♪

616
00:26:24,792 --> 00:26:26,460
[Annie] Oh, my God.

617
00:26:26,544 --> 00:26:28,087
It's Firecracker.

618
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,302
[whispering] Jesus.

619
00:26:34,385 --> 00:26:37,972
I mean, it had to be Homelander, right?

620
00:26:39,348 --> 00:26:44,020
You'd think I'd feel relieved,
but I just feel sad.

621
00:26:44,103 --> 00:26:46,188
I mean, she's a human being.

622
00:26:47,481 --> 00:26:49,650
Maybe that's why Homelander killed her.

623
00:26:51,527 --> 00:26:53,654
- [line rings]
- [modem trilling]

624
00:26:53,738 --> 00:26:55,156
That a fuckin' fax machine?

625
00:26:55,239 --> 00:26:57,283
Yeah, it's the last of the numbers
she had for him.

626
00:26:58,367 --> 00:27:02,705
Oi. 23 fucking numbers you had for
Bombsight, and they're all fucking shite?

627
00:27:02,788 --> 00:27:04,749
Do you know how to delete them?

628
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:08,377
I was telling you the truth.

629
00:27:08,461 --> 00:27:11,088
I have no idea where Bombsight is,
or how to reach him.

630
00:27:11,172 --> 00:27:12,465
So just let me go.

631
00:27:12,548 --> 00:27:15,301
Kimiko, keep an eye on her.

632
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:23,267
Fuck do we do now?

633
00:27:23,351 --> 00:27:25,978
Fetch us some pliers
and put the screws to her.

634
00:27:26,062 --> 00:27:28,522
She knows more than she's lettin' on.

635
00:27:29,774 --> 00:27:31,275
Or she doesn't.

636
00:27:31,359 --> 00:27:34,362
I'm sorry,
but she's not that good of an actress.

637
00:27:34,445 --> 00:27:35,446
He's right.

638
00:27:35,529 --> 00:27:41,035
Ooh, I know, the villain
switching sides in the final hour?

639
00:27:41,118 --> 00:27:43,412
What a twist, a shock that never happens.

640
00:27:43,496 --> 00:27:46,707
But unclench those assholes, fellas.
I'm here to help.

641
00:27:46,791 --> 00:27:48,584
I'm a free agent now.
I came alone.

642
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:50,920
You can shoot me in the heart
whenever you like.

643
00:27:51,003 --> 00:27:52,380
That's a good idea.

644
00:27:52,463 --> 00:27:56,342
That would go against our mutual interest.

645
00:27:56,425 --> 00:27:57,635
Which is?

646
00:27:57,718 --> 00:28:01,680
Stopping a petulant, laser-eyed narcissist
from also becoming immortal.

647
00:28:03,307 --> 00:28:05,976
I want him dead as much as you do.

648
00:28:06,060 --> 00:28:07,895
You spent the last couple of years
building Homelander up.

649
00:28:07,978 --> 00:28:09,647
And now you want to tear him down?

650
00:28:09,730 --> 00:28:11,190
Why the fuck should we trust you?

651
00:28:11,273 --> 00:28:13,651
You can't trust me.
Honestly, you shouldn't.

652
00:28:13,734 --> 00:28:15,027
But you will.

653
00:28:15,111 --> 00:28:16,529
And why would we do that?

654
00:28:16,612 --> 00:28:20,616
I know Campbell and Starlight
are headed to plant your little virus.

655
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:23,619
You can trace anyone,
if you know what to look for.

656
00:28:23,702 --> 00:28:27,039
And you baboons, you leave a trail
of banana peels wherever you go.

657
00:28:27,123 --> 00:28:31,210
I could have stopped you,
I could have killed you, but I didn't.

658
00:28:31,293 --> 00:28:36,298
That virus is gonna
wipe out the fuckin' lot of you.

659
00:28:36,382 --> 00:28:40,636
And you don't strike me
as the suicide type.

660
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:43,597
I will be in my nice, quiet bunker,
reading Wittgenstein in peace.

661
00:28:43,681 --> 00:28:47,977
That is, unless that bleached blonde baby

662
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:51,355
gets his hands on V1 and survives.

663
00:28:51,439 --> 00:28:54,108
You must have realized by now
granny out there

664
00:28:54,191 --> 00:28:56,277
has no clue how to contact Bombsight.

665
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:58,320
But I do.

666
00:28:58,988 --> 00:29:00,698
And I can get him here.

667
00:29:00,781 --> 00:29:03,242
So, let me help.

668
00:29:08,247 --> 00:29:11,834
Earlier today, there was a catastrophic
failure of a Vought Petroleum pipeline

669
00:29:11,917 --> 00:29:15,463
resulting in a significant amount
of crude oil spilling into the Bering Sea.

670
00:29:15,546 --> 00:29:17,047
[reporters clamoring]

671
00:29:17,131 --> 00:29:19,592
Sorry, I'm just shaking off a migraine.

672
00:29:19,675 --> 00:29:21,343
But your mind is still an open book, Chad.

673
00:29:21,427 --> 00:29:23,804
Yes, the spill was larger
than Deepwater Horizon.

674
00:29:23,888 --> 00:29:25,097
- [reporters clamoring]
- Much larger.

675
00:29:25,181 --> 00:29:27,933
No, Jimmy, we don't know
when the rupture will be sealed.

676
00:29:28,017 --> 00:29:29,018
I'm hearing weeks, at least.

677
00:29:29,101 --> 00:29:31,770
And yes, this pipeline was Deep's baby.

678
00:29:31,854 --> 00:29:34,440
Rest assured, he's got the situation
completely under control.

679
00:29:34,523 --> 00:29:37,276
I can't breathe!
I can't breathe!

680
00:29:37,359 --> 00:29:40,029
[gasps, groaning]

681
00:29:40,112 --> 00:29:42,990
[panting, groaning]

682
00:29:44,074 --> 00:29:46,243
Jeremy? No!

683
00:29:46,327 --> 00:29:49,079
No, no, no!

684
00:29:49,163 --> 00:29:51,624
No. Jeremy.

685
00:29:51,707 --> 00:29:55,002
No, no. No, no, no, no.
He's not breathing. No.

686
00:29:55,085 --> 00:29:56,962
[muttering]

687
00:29:57,046 --> 00:29:58,380
[grunting]

688
00:29:58,464 --> 00:29:59,924
Jeremy.

689
00:30:00,007 --> 00:30:01,091
[coughing]

690
00:30:01,175 --> 00:30:03,302
Jeremy? Can you hear me?

691
00:30:03,385 --> 00:30:06,013
[coughs] We know, Kevin.

692
00:30:06,096 --> 00:30:07,640
We know it was you.

693
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:10,017
[dramatic music playing]

694
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:11,727
[gasps]

695
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:14,230
♪ ♪

696
00:30:26,283 --> 00:30:29,370
Why are you so certain
Bombsight will come here?

697
00:30:29,453 --> 00:30:31,997
If I sent you a picture of Kimiko tied up,

698
00:30:32,081 --> 00:30:35,918
you'd hop here as fast as
your froggy little legs could take you.

699
00:30:36,001 --> 00:30:37,753
Park Geisha over there,

700
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:39,797
and keep an eye on her.

701
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:45,177
[wheelchair squeaking]

702
00:31:00,442 --> 00:31:04,154
I wanted to say...
I'm very sorry about this.

703
00:31:07,408 --> 00:31:10,369
I watched every episode of
Undercover Geisha when I was a kid.

704
00:31:10,452 --> 00:31:14,790
I loved it, even the parts that
were ridiculous, racist stereotypes.

705
00:31:16,458 --> 00:31:19,753
It meant so much to see
someone who looked like me on TV.

706
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:26,010
We watched with Japanese subtitles.
It's how I learned English.

707
00:31:26,093 --> 00:31:29,054
If you're such a big fan, let me go.

708
00:31:29,138 --> 00:31:31,557
Désolé, but we cannot.

709
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,268
Not until we get the V1
that Bombsight possesses.

710
00:31:34,351 --> 00:31:37,062
Wait, that's what you're after?

711
00:31:37,146 --> 00:31:38,397
V1?

712
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:41,358
[laughing]

713
00:31:41,442 --> 00:31:43,819
What-What's so funny?

714
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:46,655
I'll tell Bombsight
to just give it to you.

715
00:31:46,739 --> 00:31:48,657
I sure as hell don't want it.

716
00:31:51,785 --> 00:31:54,580
He stole the V1 for you,

717
00:31:54,663 --> 00:31:56,832
so you two could be together forever.

718
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,547
But you didn't take it.

719
00:32:05,007 --> 00:32:06,216
I said no.

720
00:32:07,509 --> 00:32:08,886
Which is why he left.

721
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:14,850
I guess, for him,
watching me get old was too painful.

722
00:32:17,227 --> 00:32:20,689
I'm sorry, I do not understand.
Why won't you take it?

723
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:23,609
To live forever?

724
00:32:25,277 --> 00:32:26,737
It'd be torture.

725
00:32:28,489 --> 00:32:30,157
[scoffs softly]

726
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:32,743
You're both so young.
You wouldn't understand.

727
00:32:33,827 --> 00:32:35,037
Maybe I would.

728
00:32:40,668 --> 00:32:43,796
Summer is only beautiful

729
00:32:43,879 --> 00:32:46,048
when you know winter is coming.

730
00:32:50,344 --> 00:32:52,346
[sentimental music playing]

731
00:32:59,061 --> 00:33:01,105
Is this how you feel?

732
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:09,238
Annie and I talked about it.

733
00:33:10,614 --> 00:33:12,199
We'd have to...

734
00:33:18,414 --> 00:33:25,796
We'd have to watch you
and Hughie waste away.

735
00:33:27,631 --> 00:33:31,677
Neither of us wants to die, but...

736
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:34,012
we don't want to be vampires, either.

737
00:33:34,096 --> 00:33:36,098
♪ ♪

738
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:41,687
I'm sorry. I hadn't, um...

739
00:33:41,770 --> 00:33:43,313
It's okay.

740
00:33:43,397 --> 00:33:45,816
We're both willing to do it anyway.

741
00:33:47,651 --> 00:33:49,570
For you.

742
00:34:06,253 --> 00:34:07,588
Jesus Christ.

743
00:34:07,671 --> 00:34:10,215
[Annie] Yeah, that's pretty much
what he was going for.

744
00:34:14,011 --> 00:34:16,013
- [bag unzipping]
- Do I even need to say be careful?

745
00:34:16,096 --> 00:34:17,222
It's okay.

746
00:34:17,306 --> 00:34:19,725
It won't go off until the timer does.

747
00:34:19,808 --> 00:34:20,976
I think.

748
00:34:24,521 --> 00:34:25,731
[Annie sighs]

749
00:34:40,037 --> 00:34:42,623
- [beeps]
- [Oh Father] Starlight...

750
00:34:42,706 --> 00:34:44,041
[door closes]

751
00:34:44,124 --> 00:34:46,960
I was wondering who befouled
the security cameras.

752
00:34:47,044 --> 00:34:48,212
Hi, Aaron.

753
00:34:48,295 --> 00:34:49,838
It's been a while.

754
00:34:49,922 --> 00:34:54,676
The Lord is working in
His most mysterious ways this evening.

755
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:57,513
I didn't think I would ever see you
in a house of worship again.

756
00:34:57,596 --> 00:35:01,141
Yeah, well, I didn't think I would ever
see you meat-riding Homelander so hard,

757
00:35:01,225 --> 00:35:04,478
but... I guess we're both
just full of surprises, aren't we?

758
00:35:04,561 --> 00:35:07,815
- I take it you're not here to repent.
- No.

759
00:35:07,898 --> 00:35:10,526
I'm here to... to talk sense
into an old friend.

760
00:35:11,276 --> 00:35:12,820
You did that for me, do you remember?

761
00:35:12,903 --> 00:35:14,279
When, um... [chuckles]

762
00:35:14,363 --> 00:35:17,491
Alex and I were gonna get those matching
tattoos and you talked us out of it.

763
00:35:17,574 --> 00:35:19,785
A tramp stamp crucifix
is a bit of a mixed message.

764
00:35:19,868 --> 00:35:22,538
Especially on a shit-faced 15-year-old.

765
00:35:22,621 --> 00:35:26,667
But if memory serves,
you weren't so grateful at the time.

766
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:29,044
Yeah, you know, it's hard to hear
that you're making a mistake

767
00:35:29,127 --> 00:35:31,505
you could regret for
the rest of your life.

768
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:37,135
But... I...

769
00:35:37,219 --> 00:35:40,681
God, I wanted your approval
so badly back then.

770
00:35:40,764 --> 00:35:44,768
You know, you were like
a cool older brother that I never had.

771
00:35:44,852 --> 00:35:48,063
And you weren't cynical, like Ezekiel.

772
00:35:49,606 --> 00:35:53,402
You... you believed.

773
00:35:55,028 --> 00:35:56,530
I still do.

774
00:35:56,613 --> 00:35:58,240
In Homelander?

775
00:35:59,533 --> 00:36:00,784
Come on, Aaron.

776
00:36:01,869 --> 00:36:04,413
You know, I started preaching
when I was nine years old,

777
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:06,915
in that moldy tent in Greenwood.

778
00:36:08,292 --> 00:36:09,918
And people would come and...

779
00:36:10,002 --> 00:36:13,046
beg me to pray for them,

780
00:36:13,130 --> 00:36:15,215
heal their illness,

781
00:36:15,299 --> 00:36:17,593
look after their children,

782
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:19,219
get them a job.

783
00:36:19,887 --> 00:36:23,640
And I raised my hands in prayer
for each of them.

784
00:36:24,558 --> 00:36:26,393
Those prayers went unanswered.

785
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,647
Nobody was listening.

786
00:36:30,731 --> 00:36:32,608
God checked out.

787
00:36:32,691 --> 00:36:35,652
Homelander is standing in front of us.

788
00:36:35,736 --> 00:36:37,696
He's not asking for blind faith.

789
00:36:37,779 --> 00:36:40,824
And when I talk...
when I talk, he listens.

790
00:36:40,908 --> 00:36:43,035
God is supposed to be selfless.

791
00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:45,245
Okay? Homelander...

792
00:36:45,329 --> 00:36:47,956
Homelander doesn't care about anyone
or anything outside of himself.

793
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:52,169
Maybe imperfect, but he...
he brought this church up out of ruin.

794
00:36:52,252 --> 00:36:55,172
He fights back against the secular forces
corrupting this nation.

795
00:36:55,255 --> 00:36:57,424
He killed Firecracker,
and you're delusional if you think

796
00:36:57,507 --> 00:36:58,842
he won't turn on you.

797
00:36:58,926 --> 00:37:02,054
Firecracker was a nonbeliever,
she brought his wrath upon herself.

798
00:37:02,137 --> 00:37:06,308
I am not afraid to stand
before Homelander's judgment!

799
00:37:12,856 --> 00:37:15,692
But you didn't sneak in here
to argue about dogma, did you?

800
00:37:18,111 --> 00:37:20,238
Oh, Annie, I am sorry.

801
00:37:22,449 --> 00:37:24,076
I really did like you.

802
00:37:25,953 --> 00:37:27,746
[muted screaming]

803
00:37:28,956 --> 00:37:29,998
[Annie groans]

804
00:37:31,541 --> 00:37:33,001
[groaning]

805
00:37:37,464 --> 00:37:38,632
[muted screaming]

806
00:37:43,679 --> 00:37:44,846
[high-pitched ringing]

807
00:37:44,930 --> 00:37:46,181
[groaning]

808
00:37:47,849 --> 00:37:49,351
[Hughie] Stop.

809
00:37:51,144 --> 00:37:53,021
You know what this is?

810
00:37:53,647 --> 00:37:56,608
I open it, you're dead in 30 seconds.

811
00:38:01,363 --> 00:38:02,614
So is Annie.

812
00:38:02,698 --> 00:38:04,658
No.

813
00:38:06,118 --> 00:38:07,911
She already took the antidote.

814
00:38:10,205 --> 00:38:12,916
You didn't go to all this trouble
just to waste that on me.

815
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,085
No...

816
00:38:15,168 --> 00:38:16,586
but I will.

817
00:38:19,464 --> 00:38:21,133
Unless you let her go.

818
00:38:30,809 --> 00:38:32,394
Don't be a stranger, Annie.

819
00:38:32,477 --> 00:38:34,438
Room for everyone in our flock.

820
00:38:41,778 --> 00:38:44,489
[newsman] Authorities are calling it
the worst environmental disaster

821
00:38:44,573 --> 00:38:45,907
- in U.S. history.
- [crying]

822
00:38:45,991 --> 00:38:50,120
An estimated 2.5 million gallons
of crude oil have already spilled...

823
00:38:50,203 --> 00:38:51,788
Plenty of fish in the sea, bro.

824
00:38:51,872 --> 00:38:53,999
[laughing]

825
00:38:54,082 --> 00:38:56,543
But most of them are fuckin' dead.

826
00:38:56,626 --> 00:38:59,296
...Vought Petroleum promised
a thorough investigation...

827
00:38:59,379 --> 00:39:01,757
You think a fish holocaust is funny, bro?

828
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:05,052
Uh, yeah. Payback's a bitch, bitch.

829
00:39:05,135 --> 00:39:07,596
[panting]
What's that supposed to mean?

830
00:39:07,679 --> 00:39:11,266
It means I flew up to Alaska,
swam down to your dumb pipeline

831
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:13,018
and punched a hole in it.

832
00:39:13,727 --> 00:39:15,270
It wasn't even that hard.

833
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:17,147
That shit is really poorly built.

834
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:20,609
What? Why?

835
00:39:20,692 --> 00:39:24,446
You killed Adam Bourke, so I killed
a bunch of porpoises or whatever.

836
00:39:24,529 --> 00:39:26,531
Now we're even steven.

837
00:39:28,283 --> 00:39:31,119
[muttering]

838
00:39:31,203 --> 00:39:33,288
I killed one f... I killed one dude!

839
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:35,665
You killed 1.4 billion fish, motherfucker!

840
00:39:35,749 --> 00:39:39,419
One human being who was
a national treasure, asshole.

841
00:39:39,503 --> 00:39:41,588
Not just some stupid fish.

842
00:39:41,671 --> 00:39:44,424
[breathing heavily]

843
00:39:44,508 --> 00:39:46,301
They were my friends.

844
00:39:48,512 --> 00:39:50,764
Sucks to suck, dipshit.

845
00:39:50,847 --> 00:39:53,558
[soundboard voice] Stop, loser,
bro-bro-bro!

846
00:39:54,559 --> 00:39:57,104
[Black Noir] So let's record
this stupid fucking thing.

847
00:39:57,187 --> 00:39:59,606
[intense music playing]

848
00:40:05,362 --> 00:40:07,447
[grunting]

849
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:18,834
[yells]

850
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:21,169
[grunting]

851
00:40:21,253 --> 00:40:23,755
You were never my bro, bro.

852
00:40:23,839 --> 00:40:24,965
[grunting]

853
00:40:30,679 --> 00:40:32,681
[breathing heavily]

854
00:40:40,021 --> 00:40:41,523
No.

855
00:40:49,489 --> 00:40:50,991
[exhales] Oh, God.

856
00:40:58,248 --> 00:40:59,541
Oh, God.

857
00:41:02,127 --> 00:41:03,670
[door slams]

858
00:41:08,300 --> 00:41:11,970
Hey. Some kid shit on the floor
in the men's room. Again.

859
00:41:12,053 --> 00:41:14,472
[sighs] Terrific.

860
00:41:17,642 --> 00:41:19,311
[laser blasting]

861
00:41:19,394 --> 00:41:20,478
[body thuds]

862
00:41:26,985 --> 00:41:32,616
Bubelah. You might not remember,
but we actually met, back-back in the day.

863
00:41:32,699 --> 00:41:34,659
You must have been yay-high,
but you know what?

864
00:41:34,743 --> 00:41:37,913
I-I saw greatness in you, even then.

865
00:41:37,996 --> 00:41:39,706
I don't remember that, Chet.

866
00:41:39,789 --> 00:41:42,584
[scoffs] I did.

867
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:44,920
- Um...
- Well,

868
00:41:45,003 --> 00:41:47,172
we needed to talk in private.

869
00:41:47,255 --> 00:41:48,882
Okay.

870
00:41:48,965 --> 00:41:54,054
I take it you saw the security footage
from the old folks' home.

871
00:41:54,137 --> 00:41:56,932
And you probably got
the very reasonable impression

872
00:41:57,015 --> 00:42:00,518
that I'm somehow working
with Butcher and them.

873
00:42:00,602 --> 00:42:02,896
Uh, but honestly?

874
00:42:02,979 --> 00:42:04,481
Fuck those guys.

875
00:42:04,564 --> 00:42:07,442
Fuck 'em. I'm on your--
I'm on Team You, big guy.

876
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:11,529
And-and-and, I mean, I'll gladly
tell you any-anything you want to know.

877
00:42:11,613 --> 00:42:13,657
[tense music playing]

878
00:42:17,035 --> 00:42:18,036
Great.

879
00:42:19,663 --> 00:42:21,081
That's great.

880
00:42:25,001 --> 00:42:26,002
[lighter flicks]

881
00:42:28,255 --> 00:42:29,965
- Tell me somethin'.
- Hmm?

882
00:42:30,048 --> 00:42:31,216
You got all this figured out.

883
00:42:31,299 --> 00:42:35,136
But you still end up trapped in a bunker
eating canned tuna and Chef Boyardee?

884
00:42:35,220 --> 00:42:36,638
Ooh, Crunchwraps, please.

885
00:42:36,721 --> 00:42:40,100
And, uh, solitude...

886
00:42:40,183 --> 00:42:42,435
is all I ever wanted.

887
00:42:42,519 --> 00:42:44,729
Since way before
Homelander knocked on my door.

888
00:42:44,813 --> 00:42:48,441
It's... gonna be magnificent.

889
00:42:48,525 --> 00:42:50,026
You're fuckin' crazier than I thought.

890
00:42:50,110 --> 00:42:51,403
And I thought you were fuckin' crazy.

891
00:42:51,486 --> 00:42:55,782
Sorry, are you not working day and night
to drop a genocidal virus?

892
00:42:55,865 --> 00:42:58,535
Yeah, but I ain't gotta enjoy it.

893
00:42:58,618 --> 00:43:01,955
- I just gotta do it.
- Don't pretend you're better than me.

894
00:43:02,038 --> 00:43:04,666
Enjoy it, don't enjoy it...

895
00:43:04,749 --> 00:43:06,584
it's still mass murder.

896
00:43:07,877 --> 00:43:09,838
Least I'm honest about it.

897
00:43:18,888 --> 00:43:22,392
[rumbling]

898
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:29,316
- Right on cue.
- [whooshing]

899
00:43:36,448 --> 00:43:38,450
[dramatic music playing]

900
00:43:42,495 --> 00:43:45,498
Oi, Bombsight, glad you could pop in.

901
00:43:45,582 --> 00:43:47,375
Get the fuck away from her.

902
00:43:47,459 --> 00:43:49,711
Lookin' pretty spry
for a hundred years old.

903
00:43:49,794 --> 00:43:52,047
When you blow your load,
is it just a puff of dust?

904
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:53,381
[Bombsight] You motherfuckers,

905
00:43:53,465 --> 00:43:55,592
I'm going to rip
every one of you to pieces.

906
00:43:55,675 --> 00:43:57,177
Try it.

907
00:43:59,054 --> 00:44:02,515
And you'll be wiping your better half's
better half off your fucking face.

908
00:44:06,019 --> 00:44:10,231
Now, how's about we just cool our jets

909
00:44:10,315 --> 00:44:15,195
and you and I have a little chin wag
like proper gentlemen.

910
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:24,579
- [Homelander sighs]
- [The Legend] Okay. Um...

911
00:44:27,165 --> 00:44:28,625
- No one here.
- I grant you,

912
00:44:28,708 --> 00:44:30,168
it-it looks like that, yeah.

913
00:44:30,251 --> 00:44:33,838
But this-this is their hideout,
so I'm sure there's plenty of clues

914
00:44:33,922 --> 00:44:35,173
- all over here.
- Oh, come on.

915
00:44:35,256 --> 00:44:37,342
- Here you go.
- [sighs]

916
00:44:37,425 --> 00:44:39,052
Oh, no, well, this is nothing,

917
00:44:39,135 --> 00:44:41,471
but, you know, they have to
have left something behind.

918
00:44:41,554 --> 00:44:42,555
You know?

919
00:44:45,433 --> 00:44:46,476
Hmm.

920
00:44:49,062 --> 00:44:50,313
It's not nothing.

921
00:44:51,856 --> 00:44:53,108
It's a Taco Bell receipt.

922
00:44:53,191 --> 00:44:54,901
No. This is Sage!

923
00:44:54,984 --> 00:44:56,361
Taunting me.

924
00:44:56,444 --> 00:44:57,529
Okay.

925
00:45:00,573 --> 00:45:02,700
[Homelander laughing]

926
00:45:07,956 --> 00:45:10,959
This makes no sense.
This makes no sense.

927
00:45:12,210 --> 00:45:15,171
This makes no sense. [laughs]

928
00:45:15,255 --> 00:45:18,633
You... you said I would get the V1.

929
00:45:18,716 --> 00:45:21,010
You said I'd be a god.

930
00:45:21,094 --> 00:45:23,638
Did I do something wrong? Did I fail you?

931
00:45:23,721 --> 00:45:25,890
I did everything you asked me to.

932
00:45:25,974 --> 00:45:27,434
I gave my boy up.

933
00:45:28,518 --> 00:45:31,062
Please don't leave me here to just rot.

934
00:45:31,146 --> 00:45:35,233
Don't-- Just let me
become nothing, like him?

935
00:45:36,734 --> 00:45:38,278
[sighs]

936
00:45:38,361 --> 00:45:39,779
Please.

937
00:45:41,489 --> 00:45:44,325
Got to assume...

938
00:45:44,409 --> 00:45:48,788
the only reason
you're saying all this stuff is you're...

939
00:45:48,872 --> 00:45:51,791
you're not gonna let me
walk out of here alive. Are you?

940
00:45:53,126 --> 00:45:54,794
Yeah.

941
00:45:54,878 --> 00:45:56,129
Okay.

942
00:45:57,380 --> 00:45:58,756
Yeah.

943
00:46:01,676 --> 00:46:04,262
All right, look, kid,

944
00:46:04,345 --> 00:46:07,724
I-I-I've been around a long time, and I...

945
00:46:10,268 --> 00:46:12,353
This is just how it goes.

946
00:46:12,437 --> 00:46:15,607
You know, all those old Supes at the home,

947
00:46:15,690 --> 00:46:17,817
every one of them had their moment
in the sun,

948
00:46:17,901 --> 00:46:20,361
and they all thought
it was gonna go on forever.

949
00:46:20,445 --> 00:46:24,324
And every one of them got shoved out
at the end.

950
00:46:25,116 --> 00:46:28,244
They all got shoved out. All of them.

951
00:46:29,537 --> 00:46:31,498
And I know what I'm talking about.

952
00:46:33,458 --> 00:46:34,918
I did the shoving.

953
00:46:36,628 --> 00:46:38,046
I mean, look at Goldie.

954
00:46:38,129 --> 00:46:42,175
One minute she's on the set
of Undercover Geisha

955
00:46:42,258 --> 00:46:44,427
getting finger-popped by Lorenzo Lamas,

956
00:46:44,511 --> 00:46:47,055
the next she's shilling
for VoughtAlert necklaces

957
00:46:47,138 --> 00:46:49,807
and Activia poop-yogurt.

958
00:46:50,517 --> 00:46:52,435
Geisha sells VoughtAlert necklaces?

959
00:46:52,519 --> 00:46:54,562
Guess you don't
watch your own news channel?

960
00:46:55,855 --> 00:46:59,901
Point is, look, there comes a day
I got shoved out, too.

961
00:46:59,984 --> 00:47:02,695
Never saw it coming,
did not see that coming.

962
00:47:02,779 --> 00:47:04,364
And I fought it like hell,

963
00:47:04,447 --> 00:47:07,534
but in the end, bupkis.

964
00:47:09,327 --> 00:47:12,080
There's a natural order to things,

965
00:47:12,163 --> 00:47:15,959
and the more you fight the inevitable,

966
00:47:16,042 --> 00:47:20,255
the more the inevitable just
cunt-punts you.

967
00:47:24,050 --> 00:47:25,176
Yep.

968
00:47:30,431 --> 00:47:33,017
You're not scared of me.

969
00:47:33,101 --> 00:47:36,563
No, I'm not scared of you. I...

970
00:47:36,646 --> 00:47:38,022
I feel for you, kid.

971
00:47:38,940 --> 00:47:39,941
I do.

972
00:47:41,568 --> 00:47:43,319
You're a fuckin' whack-job.

973
00:47:44,404 --> 00:47:48,741
But, you know, that's talent, so...

974
00:47:48,825 --> 00:47:51,119
no surprise there.

975
00:47:54,664 --> 00:47:56,541
So, there you go.

976
00:47:57,792 --> 00:47:59,586
Do what you gotta do.

977
00:48:01,421 --> 00:48:02,463
[The Legend sighs]

978
00:48:06,092 --> 00:48:07,427
You can go.

979
00:48:10,471 --> 00:48:11,848
- I can go?
- Leave.

980
00:48:11,931 --> 00:48:13,224
No words. Just go.

981
00:48:13,308 --> 00:48:14,392
Now. Go.

982
00:48:14,475 --> 00:48:16,978
- Now!
- Yeah, yeah. Yeah, yeah.

983
00:48:26,613 --> 00:48:27,697
[phone clicks]

984
00:48:30,450 --> 00:48:34,245
[line ringing]

985
00:48:34,329 --> 00:48:35,788
[man] How can I help you, sir?

986
00:48:35,872 --> 00:48:38,750
I need the tracking coordinates
for a VoughtAlert necklace.

987
00:48:40,168 --> 00:48:42,170
[uneasy music playing]

988
00:48:46,382 --> 00:48:48,259
[Mother's Milk] Look,
all we're after is the V1.

989
00:48:48,343 --> 00:48:51,721
You hand that over
and we all go home happy.

990
00:48:55,475 --> 00:48:56,976
I can't.

991
00:48:57,894 --> 00:48:58,936
- Robbie...
- No.

992
00:48:59,020 --> 00:49:00,855
You'll change your mind.

993
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:03,816
I've watched enough friends
get old and die to know,

994
00:49:03,900 --> 00:49:05,318
you'll change your mind.

995
00:49:05,401 --> 00:49:06,444
I'm sorry.

996
00:49:07,445 --> 00:49:08,446
But I won't.

997
00:49:11,074 --> 00:49:13,576
That doesn't mean we can't be together.

998
00:49:14,661 --> 00:49:18,081
We've wasted years already.

999
00:49:24,587 --> 00:49:28,383
If I gave it to you,
what would you do with it?

1000
00:49:28,466 --> 00:49:29,550
We will destroy it.

1001
00:49:30,802 --> 00:49:32,011
She is right.

1002
00:49:35,181 --> 00:49:36,641
It is a curse.

1003
00:49:40,603 --> 00:49:42,230
- No.
- [Butcher] Listen, mate.

1004
00:49:42,313 --> 00:49:45,817
You can sort things out
with the missus later,

1005
00:49:45,900 --> 00:49:48,361
but you ain't
leaving here with that shite.

1006
00:49:48,444 --> 00:49:50,321
You think I'm stupid enough
to bring it with me?

1007
00:49:50,405 --> 00:49:52,281
[Sage] You're exactly that stupid.

1008
00:49:52,365 --> 00:49:55,451
You thought Geisha's life was in danger,
you brought the V1 to save her.

1009
00:49:55,535 --> 00:49:57,245
It's the bulge in your left pocket.

1010
00:50:01,666 --> 00:50:03,126
Hmm.

1011
00:50:11,843 --> 00:50:13,261
[grunting]

1012
00:50:14,053 --> 00:50:15,054
[Kimiko] Hey.

1013
00:50:25,982 --> 00:50:28,860
- [straining]
- Robbie, just give him what he wants.

1014
00:50:39,120 --> 00:50:40,663
[exciting music playing]

1015
00:50:44,125 --> 00:50:46,335
[bullets ricocheting]

1016
00:50:47,754 --> 00:50:49,380
- Fuck.
- Let's go.

1017
00:51:02,059 --> 00:51:04,228
Please, don't.

1018
00:51:05,813 --> 00:51:07,064
They kidnapped you.

1019
00:51:07,148 --> 00:51:10,234
I don't want anyone else
to get hurt because of me.

1020
00:51:17,658 --> 00:51:18,701
[grunts]

1021
00:51:27,168 --> 00:51:28,294
Hiya, Robbie.

1022
00:51:28,377 --> 00:51:29,670
Ben.

1023
00:51:29,754 --> 00:51:31,839
- The fuck is he doing here?
- I texted him.

1024
00:51:32,548 --> 00:51:33,841
He's here to help.

1025
00:51:33,925 --> 00:51:36,511
- We don't need that motherfucker's help.
- Those two crackers

1026
00:51:36,594 --> 00:51:39,305
have been at each other's throats
for 80 years.

